    "Secondly, many feature importance measurements like SHAP are theoretically unable to cope with correlated features (Molnar, 2022).",
    "However, despite the heavily correlated spatial and temporal features, SHAP gradient explainer seems to have provided plausible explanations.",
    "Other studies also found evidence that SHAP works well on time series (Alsuradi et al., 2020; Theissler et al., 2022).",
    "In the case of EEG data, neighboring electrodes and neighboring time points should be highly correlated leading to clusters of most important electrodes as well as small continuous time windows.",
    "This is exactly what we found with plausible coordinates for both."
  ],
